<emphasis id="7BFF3D04FFD0FF94B5BDA104FEEEFD2D" bold="true" box="[151,326,632,658]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Key to species</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0191B29DFFD0FF94B5BDA1C2FA34FC94" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" type="key">
<keyStep id="F27FF9B3FFD0FF94B5BDA1C2FA34FC94" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<key id="3D1AB627FFD0FF94B5BDA1C2FA34FC94" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<paragraph id="4934E116FFD0FF94B5BDA1C2FA33FD4E" blockId="113.[151,1436,702,811]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<keyLead id="F27A4223FFD0FF94B5BDA1C2FA33FD4E" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<number id="FF43F331FFD0FF94B5BDA1C2FF0CFD6C" box="[151,164,702,723]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" value="1.0">1</number>
. Propodeum with carinae mostly reduced, at most with pleural and traces of lateral longitudinal carinae. 
<collectingCountry id="319CA186FFD0FF94B196A1C2FB44FD6C" box="[1212,1260,702,723]" name="India" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia orange, apex slightly dark........................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="8E8B9A95FFD0FF94B13EA1A0FA33FD4E" authority="(Schmiedeknecht, 1926)" authorityName="Schmiedeknecht" box="[1044,1435,732,753]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Xestopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracillima">
<emphasis id="7BFF3D04FFD0FF94B13EA1A0FB40FD4E" box="[1044,1256,732,753]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Xestopelta gracillima</emphasis>
(Schmiedeknecht)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4934E116FFD0FF94B5BDA185FA34FC94" blockId="113.[151,1436,702,811]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<keyLead id="F27A4223FFD0FF94B5BDA185FA34FC94" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
- Propodeum with pleural and lateral carinae usually complete, apical transverse carina partly present or at least indicated by carinulae. 
<collectingCountry id="319CA186FFD0FF94B46EA06AFEDCFC94" box="[324,372,790,811]" name="India" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia white with dark subbasal and apical bands. (Female unknown).......... 
<taxonomicName id="8E8B9A95FFD0FF94B157A06AFA34FC94" authority="(Brauns, 1896)" authorityName="Brauns" box="[1149,1436,790,811]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Xestopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexcincta">
<emphasis id="7BFF3D04FFD0FF94B157A06AFAE9FC94" box="[1149,1345,790,811]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Xestopelta sexcincta</emphasis>
(Brauns)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</key>
